<subSubSection pageId="99" pageNumber="198" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="99.[242,1474,890,1018]" pageId="99" pageNumber="198">
DESCRIPTION. — Besides the characters mentioned in the key, 
<taxonomicName box="[916,1037,890,914]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Orthorhinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="99" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruciatus">
<emphasis box="[916,1037,890,914]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="198">O. cruciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat darker as a whole and has a more abrupt declivity at the end of the dorsal part of interstria 5 and the aedeagal apex converging with an indistinct lateral sinus or concave curve (Fig. 148), the intensity of the pigmented parts around the ostium varying according to the age of the specimen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
